'''假记忆体综合症'''（{{lang-en|False memory syndrome}}，{{lang|en|FMS}}）是一个人確信的身份和人際關係與事實不符的一種[[心理疾病|心理疾病]]症狀。<ref>{{cite book | ref = harv | last = McHugh | first = PR | authorlink = Paul R. McHugh | title = Try to remember: Psychiatry's clash over meaning, memory and mind | url = https://archive.org/details/trytorememberpsy00mchu | publisher = Dana Press | isbn = 1-932594-39-6 | year = 2008| pages = [https://archive.org/details/trytorememberpsy00mchu/page/66 66]–7}}</ref>这个词语最先由{{en-link|Peter J. Freyd|Peter J. Freyd}}提出{{sfn|McHugh|2008|p=55}}，后来由{{en-link|假记忆体综合症基金会|False Memory Syndrome Foundation}}（FMSF）發揚光大。這個名詞不被任何醫學手冊（如[[ICD-10|ICD-10]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://priory.com/psych/ICD.htm | title=icd 10 codes: psychiatry | publisher=Priory Lodge Education Ltd | accessdate=21 October 2013 | archive-date=2020-09-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200906143159/https://priory.com/psych/ICD.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>或[[DSM-5|DSM-5]]<ref>{{Cite book
| first=
| last= American Psychiatric Association
| year= 2013
| title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders
| edition=Fifth
| publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing
| location=Arlington, VA
| pages= 
| isbn= 978-0-89042-555-8 }}</ref>）所認為是一種[[精神疾病|精神疾病]]<ref>{{cite book | last = Rix | first = Rebecca | title = Sexual abuse litigation: a practical resource for attorneys, clinicians, and advocates | publisher = Routledge | year = 2000 | page = 33 | isbn = 0-7890-1174-3 }}</ref>。然而，記憶可由外在影響而被重塑則是學界公認的原則<ref>Paterson, H. M., Kemp, R. I., & Forgas, J. P. (2010). "Co-witnesses, confederates, and conformity: The effects of discussion and delay on eyewitness memory.," ''Psychiatry, Psychology and Law.''</ref><ref>Loftus, Elizabeth F. ''Memory: Surprising New Insights Into How We Remember and Why We Forget'' (Reading, Mass.: Addison-Wesley Pub. Co., 1980).</ref><ref>Schacter, Daniel L. The Seven Sins of Memory : How the Mind Forgets and Remembers (Houghton Mifflin Co., 2001).</ref><ref>''Association for Psychological Science''(2008, August 20). "False Memories Affect Behavior."</ref>。

假记忆也许是[[恢复记忆疗法|恢复记忆疗法]]（在1990年代同样由FMSF定义的词语，描述了一大类倾向于创造交谈机会的疗法）的结果。對於此理論產生具有決定性影響的幾位人士包含[[法庭心理學|法庭心理学]]家{{le|Ralph Underwager|Ralph Underwager}}、[[心理学家|心理学家]]{{le|Elizabeth Loftus|Elithabeth Loftus}}和[[社會學家|社会学家]]{{le|Richard Ofshe|Richard Ofshe}}。假记忆体综合征並不被认为是一个正式的心理健康的診斷，但是记忆能被外界影响改变的原理卻被科学家压倒性的接受了。

== 定义 ==

FMS是有争议的。它並不屬於[[精神障碍诊断与统计|精神障碍诊断与统计]]中由Paul.R.Mchugh提出的FMSF的其中一種。陈述了这个概念由于相关的委员会以[[恢复记忆疗法|恢复记忆疗法]]的相信者为首，并不被第四版手册采纳的现状。

